   202	
   203	## Task Board Structure
   204	
   205	### Hierarchy
   206	
   207	```
   208	Epic → Story → Task/Bug
   209	```
   210	
   211	- **Epic** = large feature / module
   212	- **Story** = specific functionality within epic
   213	- **Task** = atomic unit of work
   214	- **Bug** = defect tracked within a story
   215	
   216	### Naming Convention
   217	
   218	**Distributed IDs** — each element gets a unique ID based on date + random hash.
   219	
   220	```
   221	EPIC-260203-a1b2c3_recording/
   222	  STORY-260203-d4e5f6_audio-capture/
   223	    TASK-260203-g7h8i9_audiorecorder-interface/
   224	    TASK-260203-j0k1l2_implementation/
   225	    BUG-260203-m3n4o5_some-bug/
   226	```
   227	
   228	Format: `{TYPE}-{YYMMDD}-{hash}_{kebab-case-name}`
   229	- `EPIC-YYMMDD-xxxxxx_name`
   230	- `STORY-YYMMDD-xxxxxx_name`
   231	- `TASK-YYMMDD-xxxxxx_name`
   232	- `BUG-YYMMDD-xxxxxx_name`
   233	
   234	Where:
   235	- `YYMMDD` — creation date (year, month, day)
   236	- `xxxxxx` — 6-character base36 hash (collision-resistant)
   237	
   238	IDs are globally unique and work in parallel environments (no counter conflicts).
   239	
   240	### Directory Layout
   241	
   242	```
   243	.task-board/
   244	├── .resources/                   # Flat resource storage (managed by CLI)
   245	│   ├── TASK-260203-g7h8i9/       # Resources keyed by element ID
   246	│   │   ├── design.md             # Precondition: input for the task
   247	│   │   └── results.md            # Outcome: work product
   248	│   └── STORY-260203-d4e5f6/
   249	│       └── research.md
   250	├── EPIC-260203-a1b2c3_recording/
   251	│   ├── README.md                 # Epic description, scope, AC
   252	│   ├── progress.md               # Status, blockedBy, checklist, notes, resource refs
   253	│   ├── STORY-260203-d4e5f6_audio-capture/
   254	│   │   ├── README.md
   255	│   │   ├── progress.md
   256	│   │   ├── TASK-260203-g7h8i9_interface/
   257	│   │   │   ├── README.md
   258	│   │   │   └── progress.md
   259	│   │   ├── TASK-260203-j0k1l2_implementation/
   260	│   │   │   ├── README.md
   261	│   │   │   └── progress.md
   262	│   │   └── BUG-260203-m3n4o5_crash-on-start/
   263	│   │       ├── README.md
   264	│   │       └── progress.md
   265	│   └── STORY-260203-p6q7r8_amplitude/
   266	│       └── ...
   267	└── EPIC-260203-s9t0u1_storage/
   268	    └── ...
   269	```
   270	
   271	No `system.md` needed — IDs are self-contained and don't require global counters.
