   536	
   537	## Tips
   538	
   539	- **Detail stories before planning** — create tasks for all stories before phase planning, so the plan shows real scope
   540	- **AC must be verifiable** — "works" is bad, "test passes" is good
   541	- **Update progress immediately** — don't defer
   542	- **Use checklist** for tracking subtasks within a task
   543	- **Bugs live in stories** — always attach to a relevant story
   544	- **Sub-agents write tests** — every sub-agent is responsible for tests in its scope
   545	- **Supervisor coordinates reviews** — coordinator must spawn/review-route child reviewer work before marking done
   546	- **Visualize at milestones** — render graphs before, during, and after execution with `task-board plan --render`
   547	- **Verify agents early** — run `task-board q 'agents()'` within 2 minutes of launch; if status not updated, stop and restart with better prompt
   548	- **Concrete IDs only** — never use placeholders like `TASK-XXX` in prompts; always use real IDs like `TASK-260203-ae3fcd`
   549	- **Human-facing references need ID + title/name** — when mentioning an epic, story, task, or bug in chat, include both so people can understand the reference without looking up the ID
   550	- **No work without a task** — every code change must be tracked on the board. If a task doesn't exist, create one first. Don't start coding then retroactively create tasks
   551	- **Parent is orchestrator, not worker** — the parent agent plans, creates/refines board items, spawns children, watches `RUN-...` handles, sends directives, and decides next routing. It must not do implementation, research, testing, docs, or review inline when a board task can be delegated.
   552	- **Do not force-fit broken assumptions** — if the clean path is blocked by a platform/API/product/architecture constraint, stop. Document the evidence and options, then ask the human or set `blocked`; do not spend more time building a tower of stubs, flags, priority rules, and tests around an invalid model.
   553	- **All task work through tracked background spawn** — every task on the board (research, analysis, implementation, testing, docs, and review) MUST be executed via `task-board spawn ... --background` which launches **separate CLI processes** (`claude -p` / `codex exec`), not internal sub-agents. `--background` is an explicit execution flag and must be present. Never use the Task tool or manual shell background agents for board work.
   554	- **Reviews are child work too** — when work reaches `to-review`, spawn `task-board spawn TASK-... --role reviewer --background`. The parent orchestrator reads the review outcome and routes the item to `done` or back to `to-dev`; it does not perform the review inline.
   555	- **`to-review` is not done** — producers must report `to-review` as "ready for review" or "handed off to review". Coordinators must not tell the human "done"/"complete"/"finished"/"final"/"готово" until a reviewer has accepted the work and the board item is actually `done`.
   556	- **Coordinators track `RUN-...`, not shell jobs** — after spawning, hold onto the returned run id and drive orchestration with `task-board spawn status/events/watch/wait`. Do not rely on `&`, `nohup`, or runtime background wrappers to track completion
   557	- **Drive unblocked tasks to terminal handoff** — if no objective blocker remains, the spawned worker must keep going until it has checked the relevant checklist items, attached outcome evidence, and moved the task to its role `end_status` (`to-review` for producers, `done` for reviewers). Do not leave tasks stalled in `analysis`, `development`, `testing`, or `reviewing`; use `blocked` only for real external blockers and document the evidence.
   558	- **Dependent children are sequenced** — if child B consumes or reviews child A's output, the parent must `spawn wait` child A, inspect status/outcome resources, and only then spawn child B. Parallel fan-out is only for independent tasks.
   559	- **`--role` is REQUIRED on spawn** — never spawn without a role. Pick the right role for the task: `researcher` for analysis, `developer` for code, `tester` for tests, `solution-architect` for decomposition, `doc-writer` for docs, `reviewer` for reviews. The role drives the agent's identity, skills, lifecycle (status transitions), and definition of done
   560	- **`project_config()` first** — before spawn or spawn-contract review, run `task-board q 'project_config()'` so you know whether the current cwd is local or remote and which shared `spawn` settings are in effect
   561	- **Resource CRUD is explicit** — `add_resource` / `resource add` create a new named resource and must not silently overwrite; use `update_resource` / `resource update` to replace an existing resource; use `delete_resource` / `resource delete` to remove one
   562	- **Inline text resources via DSL** — use `task-board m 'add_resource(...)'` for create and `task-board m 'update_resource(...)'` for replacement when the payload is short text that already fits naturally in DSL
   563	- **File and URL attachments via CLI** — use `task-board resource add TASK-... ./file.png --type precondition`, `task-board resource update TASK-... ./file.png`, and `task-board resource delete TASK-... NAME`
   564	- **Artifact names must include the task ID** — when attaching outcome artifacts or task-specific instructions, include the owning task ID in the resource name, e.g. `TASK-260218-abc123_results.md`
   565	- **Chat attachments need the bridge, not the board** — if the file exists only as a chat attachment and has no local path, install [`alexis-agents-infra`](https://github.com/relux-works/alexis-agents-infra), run `agents-attachments materialize`, then pass the resolved path into `task-board resource add`
   566	- **Precondition resources = agent instructions** — when spawning via `task-board spawn`, precondition resources are auto-injected into the agent prompt via the template
   567	- **Ignore stale `.temp` worktrees during audits** — when reviewing help/docs/source for spawn drift, search canonical source paths with `.temp/**` excluded; historical `.temp/*/skill-project-management-worktree/` copies can contain obsolete spawn files
   568	- **Research goes to `.research/` AND resources** — all research results persist in `.research/{YYMMDD}_{topic}.md` (project-level) AND as outcome resources on the task. See [`references/research-workflow.md`](references/research-workflow.md)
   569	- **Plans go to `.planning/`** — after phase planning, persist them with `task-board plan --save` to `.planning/{YYMMDD}_{HHmmss}_{topic}.md` for session recovery. See [`references/planning-workflow.md`](references/planning-workflow.md)
   570	- **Legacy token in config** — if you see `remote.token` in `task-board.config.json`, suggest running `scripts/migrate-credentials.sh --user USER_ID` to move it to the credentials store
   571	
   572	---
   573	
   574	## Remote Board Mode
   575	
   576	The board can run as a centralized web service instead of local `.task-board/` directory. Multiple agents connect to the same board via HTTP.
   577	
   578	### Setup
   579	
   580	```bash
   581	# Start board-server
   582	cd ~/src/skill-project-management/tools/board-server
   583	go run . --data-dir /tmp/board-server-data/boards --auth-db /tmp/board-server-data/auth.db --addr :8090
   584	
   585	# Set environment (token from first-run output)
   586	export TASK_BOARD_REMOTE=http://localhost:8090
   587	export TASK_BOARD_TOKEN=tb_xxxxx
   588	export TASK_BOARD_ID=my-project
   589	
   590	# Create a board
   591	curl -X POST -H "Authorization: Bearer $TASK_BOARD_TOKEN" \
   592	  -d '{"id":"my-project","name":"My Project"}' \
   593	  $TASK_BOARD_REMOTE/admin/boards
   594	
   595	# Use normally — q and m route to server automatically
   596	task-board q --format compact 'summary()'
   597	task-board m 'create(type=epic, name=my-feature)'
   598	```
   599	
   600	### How It Works
   601	
   602	- `task-board q` and `task-board m` detect `TASK_BOARD_REMOTE` env and route DSL to the server via HTTP
   603	- `task-board q 'schema()'` and `task-board q 'project_config()'` are resolved locally so agents can inspect the current repo runtime even when normal reads/writes target a remote board
   604	- All mutations (status changes, linking, assignment, auto-promotion) happen server-side
   605	- Multiple agents can work on the same board concurrently — bbolt handles serialization
   606	- `task-board resource add/update/delete/get` work in both local and remote mode for normal local-path and URL attachments
   607	- [`alexis-agents-infra`](https://github.com/relux-works/alexis-agents-infra) is only needed when the file exists only as a chat attachment and must be materialized first
   608	- `grep`, `validate`, `plan --render`, `tree` are local-only (not available in remote mode)
   609	- `spawn` reads board info via remote, but launches agent process locally
   610	- `task-board export` / `task-board import` work in both local and remote mode
   611	
   612	### Config Resolution
   613	
   614	Priority:
   615	- explicit remote: `--remote` flag > `TASK_BOARD_REMOTE` env
   616	- mode selection: `TASK_BOARD_MODE` env > `task-board.config.json` (`mode`) > default `local`
   617	- unified config path override: `TASK_BOARD_CONFIG` (otherwise `./task-board.config.json`)
   618	- mode=`remote`: use `remote` section (`url`, `board`, `tls_no_verify`) — **no token or active user in config file**
   619	- mode=`local`: use `local` section (`board_dir`, relative path)
   620	- `task-board q 'project_config()'` is the supported preflight check for agents; it shows configured mode, effective mode after explicit overrides, board source, whoami, and shared spawn settings for the current cwd
   621	
   622	Token resolution (in order):
   623	1. `TASK_BOARD_TOKEN` env
   624	2. macOS Keychain (`remote.url + selected user`)
   625	3. Error: no token — run `task-board login USER TOKEN` or set `TASK_BOARD_TOKEN`
   626	
   627	Keychain-first auth model:
   628	- project config pins only shared board context: `remote.url`, `remote.board`, `tls_no_verify`
   629	- selected user lives in non-versioned local credentials state scoped by `remote.url + remote.board` (and legacy `remote.user` is only a backward-compat fallback)
   630	- token lives in Keychain, not in git and not in `task-board.config.json`
   631	- `TASK_BOARD_TOKEN` is env override/bootstrap only, not the normal storage path
   632	- `task-board login/logout/switch-user/whoami` manage the selected-user flow
   633	
   634	Global non-versioned auth state file:
   635	- path: `~/.config/task-board/credentials.json`
   636	- shape:
   637	
   638	```json
   639	{
   640	  "remotes": {
   641	    "https://board.example.com": {
   642	      "active_user": "admin",
   643	      "active_users": {
   644	        "my-project": "alexis",
   645	        "ops-project": "admin"
   646	      },
   647	      "users": {}
   648	    }
   649	  }
   650	}
   651	```
   652	
   653	- `remotes.<url>.active_users.<board-id>` = selected user for a concrete board on that remote
   654	- `remotes.<url>.active_user` = remote-wide fallback before a board is pinned or when no board-specific selection exists
   655	- `remotes.<url>.users` = legacy metadata container; in steady state tokens should be in Keychain, not here
   656	
   657	Migration from legacy plaintext credentials:
   658	```bash
   659	task-board migrate-keychain --print-shell-cleanup
   660	task-board migrate-keychain --cleanup-legacy-file
   661	```
   662	
   663	Other:
   664	- sidecar default location: project directory (current working directory / `--project-dir` for setup scripts), not global/bin directory
   665	- setup/install write unified config into project directory (default: current dir)
   666	- CLI startup auto-bootstrap: if local board exists and config file does not exist, CLI writes default local profile (`mode=local`, `local.board_dir=.task-board`)
   667	
   668	### Board Migration Workflows
   669	
   670	Archive migration is now the canonical way to move a board between local and remote runtimes.
   671	
   672	What is preserved:
   673	- hierarchy (`epic -> story -> task/bug`)
   674	- statuses
   675	- assignee
   676	- notes/checklists/dependencies
   677	- precondition/outcome resource refs
   678	- resource payload files
   679	
   680	Core commands:
   681	```bash
   682	# Export current board to archive
   683	task-board export /tmp/board.tar.gz
   684	
   685	# Import archive into current board
   686	task-board import /tmp/board.tar.gz
   687	```
   688	
   689	#### Local -> Remote
   690	
   691	```bash
   692	# source project (local mode)
   693	cd ~/src/source-project
   694	task-board export /tmp/source-board.tar.gz
   695	
   696	# remote-connected project
   697	cd ~/src/target-project
   698	export TASK_BOARD_REMOTE=http://localhost:8080
   699	export TASK_BOARD_USER=sampleuser
   700	export TASK_BOARD_ID=my-project
   701	task-board login sampleuser tb_xxxxx
   702	task-board import /tmp/source-board.tar.gz
   703	```
   704	
   705	#### Remote -> Local
   706	
   707	```bash
   708	# remote-connected project
   709	cd ~/src/source-remote-project
   710	task-board export /tmp/remote-board.tar.gz
   711	
   712	# target local project
   713	cd ~/src/target-local-project
   714	cat > task-board.config.json <<'JSON'
   715	{
   716	  "mode": "local",
   717	  "local": {
   718	    "board_dir": ".task-board"
   719	  },
   720	  "spawn": {
   721	    "max_parallel": 20
   722	  }
   723	}
   724	JSON
   725	
   726	task-board import /tmp/remote-board.tar.gz
   727	```
   728	
   729	#### Round-trip Before Deploy
   730	
   731	Use a locally deployed `board-server` to prove `local -> remote -> local` before touching the real remote service:
   732	
   733	```bash
   734	# 1. Build a fresh board-server binary for local service validation
   735	cd ~/src/skill-project-management
   736	make install-backend
   737	
   738	# 2. Start local board-server
   739	board-server --addr 127.0.0.1:8091 --data-dir /tmp/board-server-data/boards --auth-db /tmp/board-server-data/auth.db
   740	
   741	# 3. Project-local remote config
   742	cat > task-board.config.json <<'JSON'
   743	{
   744	  "mode": "remote",
   745	  "spawn": {
   746	    "max_parallel": 20
   747	  },
   748	  "remote": {
   749	    "url": "http://127.0.0.1:8091",
   750	    "board": "roundtrip-playground",
   751	    "tls_no_verify": false
   752	  }
   753	}
   754	JSON
   755	
   756	# 4. Store token, create board, import archive
   757	task-board login admin tb_xxxxx
   758	task-board admin board-create roundtrip-playground "Roundtrip Playground"
   759	task-board import /tmp/source-board.tar.gz
   760	
   761	# 5. Export back out and import into a fresh local board
   762	task-board export /tmp/roundtrip.tar.gz
   763	```
   764	
   765	For local-deployed service mode, if MinIO is not configured, `board-server` automatically uses a filesystem resource backend under `<dataDir>/.resources/`. That is the easiest way to validate resource payload round-trip during development.
   766	
   767	---
   768	
   769	## Setup & Deployment
   770	
   771	Two deployment modes. Choose based on your use case:
   772	
   773	| | Local | Service |
   774	|---|---|---|
   775	| **Board storage** | `.task-board/` directory in project | board-server (bbolt + MinIO) |
   776	| **Multi-agent** | Single agent at a time | Multiple agents concurrently |
   777	| **Persistence** | Git (committed with project) | Server-side (backed up separately) |
   778	| **Network** | None | HTTP (LAN or remote) |
   779	| **Setup time** | Zero — just use CLI | 2 min (make) or 5 min (Docker) |
   780	| **Best for** | Solo dev, small projects | Teams, swarm agents, persistent boards |
   781	
   782	### Local mode (default)
   783	
   784	No board bootstrap needed. CLI creates `.task-board/` on first `create` command.
   785	If you run setup/install scripts, profile configs are created automatically:
   786	
   787	```bash
   788	# Canonical workstation setup for CLI/TUI + installed skill artifact
   789	./scripts/setup.sh --mode local --board-dir .task-board
   790	
   791	# Start using
   792	task-board m 'create(type=epic, name=my-feature, description="...")'
   793	task-board q --format compact 'summary()'
   794	```
   795	
   796	Board lives in `.task-board/` inside your project. Commit it to git for persistence.
   797	
   798	If this board lives inside a real code repository that agents will work on, bootstrap it from the `skill-project-management` source checkout with repo-local agents enabled:
   799	
   800	```bash
   801	cd /path/to/skill-project-management
   802	./scripts/setup.sh --project-dir /path/to/project --mode local --board-dir .task-board --bootstrap-local-agents
   803	```
   804	
   805	This is the expected companion step for board setup in a project repo:
   806	- `.agents/` gets the local runtime contents and templates
   807	- `.claude/` and `.codex/` are refreshed as thin links into `.agents/`
   808	- spawned agents can reliably see repo-local instructions instead of only global installs
   809	- agents can call `task-board q 'project_config()'` before work to verify whether this repo uses a local board or a remote profile
   810	
   811	### Service mode (board-server)
   812	
   813	#### Quick start (local binary)
   814	
   815	```bash
   816	# Install CLI/TUI + project profile via the canonical setup path
   817	./scripts/setup.sh --mode remote --remote-url http://localhost:8080 --remote-user sampleuser --remote-board my-project
   818	
   819	# If this board drives work in a code repo, prefer the single setup command with repo-local agents
   820	./scripts/setup.sh --project-dir /path/to/project --mode remote --remote-url http://localhost:8080 --remote-board my-project --bootstrap-local-agents
   821	
   822	# Build board-server binary (binary-only helper)
   823	make install-backend
   824	
   825	# Start server locally
   826	board-server --addr :8080 --data-dir ./data/boards --auth-db ./data/auth.db
   827	```
   828	
   829	Server prints everything you need on startup:
   830	```
   831	  board-server running:
   832	  URL:         http://localhost:8080
   833	  Data:        ./data/boards
   834	
   835	  FIRST RUN — admin token (save it, shown once):
   836	  tb_xxxxx
   837	
   838	  Quick start:
   839	    export TASK_BOARD_REMOTE=http://localhost:8080
   840	    export TASK_BOARD_ID=<board-id>

exec
/bin/zsh -lc "nl -ba /Users/alexis/.claude/skills/project-management/SKILL.md | sed -n '841,1400p'" in /Users/alexis/src/relux-works/relux-analytics
 succeeded in 0ms:
   841	```
   842	
   843	Select a user, store the token in Keychain, then go:
   844	```bash
   845	export TASK_BOARD_REMOTE=http://localhost:8080
   846	export TASK_BOARD_USER=sampleuser
   847	
   848	# Create a board
   849	task-board admin board create my-project "My Project"
   850	
   851	export TASK_BOARD_ID=my-project
   852	task-board login sampleuser tb_xxxxx
   853	
   854	# Use normally — all DSL commands route to server
   855	task-board q --format compact 'summary()'
   856	task-board m 'create(type=epic, name=auth-system)'
   857	
   858	# Optional: write remote profile config explicitly
   859	./scripts/setup.sh --mode remote --remote-url http://localhost:8080 --remote-user sampleuser --remote-board my-project
   860	```
   861	
   862	#### Docker deployment (production)
   863	
   864	Full stack: Caddy (TLS reverse proxy) + board-server + MinIO (resource storage).
   865	
   866	```bash
   867	cd tools/board-server/deploy
   868	cp .env.example .env
   869	# Edit .env: set BOARD_DOMAIN, MinIO credentials
   870	
   871	./deploy.sh         # Build + start (prints admin token on first run)
   872	./status.sh         # Check health
   873	./logs.sh           # Tail logs
   874	./backup.sh         # Backup data
   875	./stop.sh           # Stop all
   876	./e2e-test.sh       # End-to-end test
   877	```
   878	
   879	For self-signed TLS (localhost/LAN):
   880	```bash
   881	# CLI flag
   882	task-board --insecure q --format compact 'summary()'
   883	
   884	# Or environment (inherited by spawned agents)
   885	export TASK_BOARD_TLS_NO_VERIFY=1
   886	
   887	# Or unified config file (project-local)
   888	# ./task-board.config.json  (NOTE: no token here — use 'task-board login')
   889	{
   890	  "mode":"remote",
   891	  "local":{"board_dir":".task-board"},
   892	  "spawn":{"max_parallel":20},
   893	  "remote":{"url":"https://board.local","board":"my-project","tls_no_verify":true}
   894	}
   895	```
   896	
   897	#### User management (service mode)
   898	
   899	```bash
   900	# Create user + token
   901	task-board admin user create alice
   902	task-board admin token create alice
   903	
   904	# Grant board access
   905	task-board admin access grant alice my-project editor
   906	
   907	# List users
   908	task-board admin user list
   909	```
   910	
   911	Roles: `admin` (full access), `editor` (read/write board), `viewer` (read-only).
